<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12029h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12029h">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12029h"> 29(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font>gold<font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> embroidered skull cup</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Les ordonnances sur les devoirs qu&apos;on devoit rendre aux morts. C&apos;&eacute;toit, par exemple, honorer leur m&eacute;moire, que de conserver leurs cr&acirc;nes, de les faire border d&apos;or ou d&apos;argent, & de s&apos;en servir pour boire. <br><font color="green">[Instructions on the tribute to be paid to the dead. It was considered as a way of honoring their memory to preserve their skulls, trim them with gold or silver and to use it as a cup to drink.]</font> <small> M. Sabbathier, <a name="MSAD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MSAD"><cite title="source">Dictionnaire pour l'intelligence des auteurs classiques, Grecs et Latins</cite></a> (1773) 495</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
